m_q.target_metric: Name of builder(s) that had more than 7 GT numbers
sub_questions: How many GT numbers does each builder have?
Which builders have a count of GT numbers greater than 7?
How to parse the 'GT numbers' column to count individual numbers?

sources: Train Builders and their Works Numbers

unit_annotations.GT numbers: range notation (e.g., '651-705' represents multiple sequential numbers)
unit_annotations.Works numbers: range notation with possible newline separators
unit_annotations.CN numbers: range notation with possible newline separators

format_notes: GT numbers column contains ranges (e.g., '651-705') and may contain newline characters separating multiple ranges
Ranges need to be parsed to count individual numbers
Multiple ranges within a cell are separated by newline characters (\n)
Some cells contain single numbers or discontinuous ranges

constraints: GT numbers must be parsed from range notation to count individual values
Ranges like '651-705' represent consecutive numbers from 651 to 705 inclusive
Multiple ranges in a cell (separated by \n) should all be counted
Count threshold is greater than 7 (not greater than or equal to 7)
derived_filters: Parse GT numbers ranges to expand into individual counts
Calculate total count per builder by summing all ranges
Filter builders where total GT numbers count > 7
output_format_requirements: If multiple builders qualify, return all qualifying names
